    "title": "What is AI, Really?",
    "displayTitle": "What is AI, Really?",
    "body": "<p><meta></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#1f1f1f;\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><strong>AI: The Simple Definition</strong></span></b></span></h4><p>Artificial Intelligence (AI) refers to computer systems designed to <strong>mimic human intelligence</strong> to perform specific tasks. Think of AI as an advanced tool that can see patterns, make decisions, or create content based on the data it's been trained on.</p><p><strong>Key Point:</strong> Today, we exclusively use <strong>Narrow AI</strong>, meaning the system is only intelligent within a highly focused domain.</p><ul><li><strong>Narrow AI (Current):</strong> This is highly specific AI designed to perform a single, focused task.<ul><li><strong>Relatable Examples:</strong> AI software that reviews thousands of legal documents to find every instance of a specific contract clause, or an advertising platform that automatically adjusts bidding strategy.</li></ul></li><li><strong>General AI (Hypothetical):</strong> This would be an AI that can understand, learn, and apply its intelligence to solve any problem, just like a human being.</li></ul>",
    "_ariaLevel": 0,
    "_id": "6940011ae2905e45549c89f9",
    "_parentId": "69400033e2905e45549c89f8",
