    "_isA11yCompletionDescriptionEnabled": true,
    "title": "New Component Title",
    "displayTitle": "New Component Title",
    "body": "<p>The key difference between these technologies is the ability to <strong>learn and adapt</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Traditional Software</strong> follows <strong>explicit rules</strong> written by a programmer (the rules are fixed).<ul><li><i>Example:</i> A simple quiz application that scores based on pre-programmed correct answers.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Automation</strong> performs repetitive, defined steps <strong>without learning</strong> (the steps are predictable).<ul><li><i>Example:</i> A mail-merge tool that automatically fills in a customer's name and company in an email template.</li></ul></li><li><strong>AI</strong> learns from <strong>data and feedback</strong> to improve its own rules and performance over time (the rules are adaptive).<ul><li><i>Example:</i> A system that learns your writing style and suggests structural improvements or alternative phrasing.</li></ul></li></ul>",
    "_ariaLevel": 0,
    "_id": "6940032ce2905e45549c8a01",
    "_parentId": "69400282e2905e45549c89fe",
