    "title": "New Component Title",
    "displayTitle": "New Component Title",
    "body": "<p>To function, AI systems need two things: <strong>data</strong> and a <strong>model</strong>. The core mechanism is <strong>Pattern Recognition</strong>.</p><h4><strong>Data is the Fuel</strong></h4><p>AI learning starts with massive amounts of dataâ€”this is the <strong>training set</strong>. For example, a system trained to assist a teacher is fed thousands of previously graded exams and essays.</p><h4><strong>Pattern Recognition: The Core Mechanism</strong></h4><ol><li><strong>Prediction:</strong> Based on the patterns it learned, the AI model calculates the most statistically probable or appropriate output (e.g., suggesting a score, drafting a summary).</li><li><strong>Feedback &amp; Refinement:</strong> Humans or the system itself evaluate the output. If the prediction was wrong, the system subtly adjusts its internal settings to make a better prediction next time. This process is called <strong>iteration</strong>.</li></ol>",
    "_ariaLevel": 0,
    "_id": "69400367e2905e45549c8a03",
